'''Viserion''' is one of the [[dragons]] born in the [[Dothraki Sea]], along with [[Drogon]] and [[Rhaegal]]. He is named after [[Daenerys Targaryen]]'s brother, [[Viserys Targaryen|Viserys]]. He is distinguishable by his cream and gold colored scales, and red-orange wings.

sections.In the books:
In the ''[[A Song of Ice and Fire]]'' novels, Viserion is much the same. In contrast to his namesake, Viserion is noted as being the best behaved of Daenerys's three dragons, even compared to his brother Rhaegal. He is also the most friendly to other people besides Daenerys herself. His primary coloration is specifically cream, though he is often referred to as simply the &quot;white&quot; dragon.

Daenerys named Viserion after her brother [[Viserys Targaryen|Viserys]]. As she explained, &quot;Viserys was cruel and weak and frightened, yet he was my brother still. His dragon will do what he could not.&quot;

Viserion's name hasn't been mentioned on-screen as of the end of Season 4, though it is stated in the Season 4 HBO Viewer's Guide, establishing that his name is the same in the TV continuity.&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season-4/episode-10/houses/5/house-targaryen ]&lt;/ref&gt;

